Who'd be crazy enough to steal a cop car?

31:30.080 --> 31:33.440
You don't know, do you?
- Don't know what?

31:33.440 --> 31:35.560
We don't know anything.
Nothing works, 

31:35.560 --> 31:37.360
the TV, the radio, the phone.

31:37.360 --> 31:41.320
I'm running out of time.
- Hold on there, fella.

31:41.320 --> 31:44.280
You better start talking or
get the hell out of here.

31:49.800 --> 31:52.200
Dad, just tell him you're sorry.

31:57.200 --> 31:59.440
Now I'm sure you don't
want to go spilling blood

31:59.440 --> 32:03.320
for no good reason, in front
of all these decent people.

32:03.320 --> 32:08.920
What do you say? Just let Bob go and then
you will be on your way, nice and easy.

32:25.000 --> 32:26.920
They're here.

32:28.760 --> 32:31.040
You're gonna need this.

32:31.600 --> 32:33.920
Wait, who's here?
- More like her.

32:33.920 --> 32:36.360
What do you mean like her?

32:44.080 --> 32:46.680
Hold on. I don't think
that's such a good idea.

32:46.680 --> 32:50.600
Dad, I can handle it.
- He can handle it.

32:50.600 --> 32:52.600
He doesn't have a choice.

32:58.240 --> 33:00.280
Don't do anything brave.

33:05.480 --> 33:08.200
What's happening?
- Better get back inside.

33:18.880 --> 33:20.800
Jeep, come on!

33:51.660 --> 33:53.700
Everybody stay calm!

33:58.420 --> 34:00.900
Okay, we're locked in here,
so what the fuck we're doin' now?

34:20.659 --> 34:24.100
All right, Rambo. You got us up here.
You mind telling us what we're fighting?

34:24.100 --> 34:26.659
Listen!

34:27.620 --> 34:29.620
You hear what I'm hearing?

34:33.659 --> 34:37.260
What the hell is that?
- Sounds almost like...

34:37.260 --> 34:39.260
Ice cream?

34:45.940 --> 34:47.860
Can't be fucking serious, right?

34:48.179 --> 34:50.940
There's a safety switch on the side of your weapon, 

34:50.940 --> 34:52.980
push it all the way down., two clicks.

34:52.980 --> 34:54.980
Now when this starts, you hold on tight.

34:54.980 --> 35:00.900
Otherwise you're gonna blow your hand off.

35:00.900 --> 35:02.900
What the fuck are you all looking at me for?

35:27.460 --> 35:34.860
Audrey. Honey, listen.
It's the Ice Cream Man.

36:09.780 --> 36:11.900
Oh, man, he don't look that bad.

36:12.940 --> 36:14.860
Oh shit, oh shit, oh shit.

36:16.620 --> 36:18.540
Oh, damn it!

36:18.540 --> 36:20.460
Get ready.

36:42.040 --> 36:43.960
Is that it?

37:06.480 --> 37:08.400
Now! Shoot now!

38:33.520 --> 38:37.040
They're just regular people.
- Not anymore! Keep firing!

38:56.860 --> 38:58.980
Don't let them get near the windows.

39:24.200 --> 39:26.120
Howard!

39:33.980 --> 39:36.220
See what you made me do, mother?

39:47.600 --> 39:49.520
There you are!

40:11.120 --> 40:13.800
We got them running.

40:14.200 --> 40:17.320
Let me go! He's alive!
He's out there!

40:17.320 --> 40:20.840
He's out there.
- He's gone.

40:27.160 --> 40:29.080
You okay?

40:29.560 --> 40:31.480
Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

40:34.280 --> 40:36.200
Thanks.

40:36.360 --> 40:39.120
I told you not to do anything brave.

40:43.160 --> 40:45.080
We got them running.

40:47.800 --> 40:50.440
What happened?
- Someone needs to be on the roof.

40:50.940 --> 40:53.020
I'll go.
- Hold on.

40:55.180 --> 40:57.260
You better start talking.

41:02.780 --> 41:08.820
The last time God lost faith
in man he sent a flood.

41:10.700 --> 41:13.180
This time, he sent
what you see outside.

41:13.180 --> 41:15.620
Are you saying this is the Apocalypse?

41:15.620 --> 41:18.140
I'm saying this is an extermination.

41:19.260 --> 41:22.100
Those things outside are just vessels,

41:22.380 --> 41:25.900
they're possessed ,
the weakest willed are the easiest to turn.

41:25.900 --> 41:29.380
Possessed by what?
Demons?

41:29.380 --> 41:31.300
No...

41:34.980 --> 41:37.700
By angels.

41:37.900 --> 41:42.500
Hold on. I don't know what
book you've been reading

41:42.500 --> 41:47.980
but in my version the
angels are good guys.

41:47.980 --> 41:50.580
Well the truth, I'm afraid,
is never that simple.

41:50.580 --> 41:54.020
Bullshit. I'm not a pastor,
but I've never heard of no

41:54.020 --> 41:58.740
Ice Cream Man, or old lady eating raw meat,
jumping on the ceiling with baby teeth.

41:58.740 --> 42:03.660
So I don't know what the so much about them?
- Hold on. How do you know so much about them?

42:04.460 --> 42:07.380
Because until last night,
I was on their side.

42:07.380 --> 42:09.300
So you're saying you...
- Yeah, yeah, that's right.

42:09.300 --> 42:11.740
Yesterday I was fucking Santa Claus.

42:11.740 --> 42:15.260
You know this is crazy, right?
I mean....

42:15.260 --> 42:17.180
I don't even believe in God.

42:17.180 --> 42:19.980
Well that's just fine, Bob, he
doesn't believe in you either.

42:20.340 --> 42:23.340
He doesn't believe in
any of this anymore.

42:23.340 --> 42:26.860
I knew this day was coming,
I just didn't think I'd be around to see it.

42:26.860 --> 42:29.100
Come on, Percy!
What are we even talking about this for?

42:29.100 --> 42:34.740
Angels, and possessed people.
It's not real! It's...

42:34.740 --> 42:37.100
Have you looked outside, Bob?

42:37.380 --> 42:42.580
I mean , those people aren't exactly
our regular customers!

42:44.760 --> 42:47.280
So, are you here to protect us?

42:47.920 --> 42:49.840
No, not you.

42:50.600 --> 42:52.520
Her.

42:53.040 --> 42:56.160
Me? 
Why me?

42:56.160 --> 43:00.040
Because your child is the
only hope humanity has of survival.

43:08.480 --> 43:10.880
Wait just a minute, 
this can't be happening

43:10.880 --> 43:13.160
I'm nobody, 
I'm just a waitress.

43:15.120 --> 43:18.640
I don't even own a car.
- None of that matters anymore.

43:18.640 --> 43:21.720
Either your child lives
or mankind dies.

43:23.520 --> 43:26.280
So we're supposed to hold those things off
until the baby gets here?

43:26.280 --> 43:28.200
That's it.

43:28.200 --> 43:30.120
I'm only eight months pregnant.

43:30.120 --> 43:32.040
This shit can't be happening, man.

43:32.040 --> 43:34.920
How are we supposed to
survive here for a month?

43:34.920 --> 43:37.120
We won't have to.

43:39.080 --> 43:42.560
It's coming soon, isn't it?
- Yes.

43:45.100 --> 43:49.300
Listen. I simply don't care
what you people believe.

43:49.300 --> 43:51.660
And those things outside,
they don't care either.

43:51.660 --> 43:54.180
They just want the child dead. 

43:55.500 --> 43:58.020
Now, this first attack was
a test of our strength.

43:58.020 --> 44:01.260
The next will be a test
of our weakness.

44:01.820 --> 44:04.420
Now we can sit here and discuss it 

44:04.420 --> 44:06.620
or you can try to help me.

44:06.980 --> 44:12.460
But believe me. Something
much worse is on the way.

44:22.460 --> 44:24.540
Sons of bitches.

44:26.060 --> 44:28.620
They're out there,
I can feel them.

44:35.140 --> 44:39.140
So what's with that gun?
- What?

44:39.140 --> 44:43.540
Your piece. The one you
killed grandma with.

44:43.540 --> 44:46.340
Don't reckon it's for
hunting buck.

44:48.300 --> 44:53.260
I use it for protection.
- Protection from what?

44:53.260 --> 44:55.620
From people.
- People?

44:57.300 --> 45:01.180
People that be starting shit.
- Regular people, or just...

45:01.180 --> 45:05.020
No. Not regular regular
people, but you know...

45:05.020 --> 45:07.260
Irregular people, then.

45:08.160 --> 45:10.440
Get the fuck out of here, man.

45:11.800 --> 45:15.280
I got my reasons for doing
what I do, and that's that.

45:25.960 --> 45:28.560
I've never actually
used it, all right?

45:30.320 --> 45:34.840
I may have flashed it, scared a few
folks but, 

45:34.840 --> 45:37.920
it never actually fired off.

45:40.680 --> 45:42.720
Not until today.

45:47.240 --> 45:49.800
This shit is crazy, man.

45:55.200 --> 45:57.320
When I was a kid...

45:57.320 --> 46:01.000
my father would sit by my bed every night

46:01.000 --> 46:03.560
before I went to sleep.

46:06.200 --> 46:10.280
And he'd say to me:

46:12.720 --> 46:19.440
"Percy, if you don't wake up tomorrow,

46:21.200 --> 46:27.280
if it turns out that today

46:27.280 --> 46:31.120
is your last day on earth.

46:32.160 --> 46:35.640
Will you be proud of 

46:35.640 --> 46:38.560
what you've done in this life?

46:40.840 --> 46:46.080
cuz if you ain't...

46:47.960 --> 46:52.240
you better start
getting square."

47:07.760 --> 47:09.680
Fuck it.

47:25.920 --> 47:29.440
On the house.
- Thank you.

47:33.200 --> 47:36.640
You hungry?
- No.

47:37.240 --> 47:41.040
Just because it's the end of the world
doesn't mean you have to starve.

47:41.520 --> 47:44.520
I'm just happy we still have the gas on.

47:56.460 --> 47:59.500
I never really cared much for beer..

48:01.460 --> 48:04.420
Howard was the beer 
drinker in the family.

48:17.340 --> 48:23.500
So what did you do? 
You know before you came here.

48:23.900 --> 48:29.700
I was a soldier.
A general in His army.

48:32.980 --> 48:36.340
So what changed?
What made you leave?

48:36.660 --> 48:39.380
I was given an order
I didn't believe in.

48:42.020 --> 48:45.820
He lost faith. 
I didn't.

48:52.340 --> 48:54.780
How come you still have faith?

48:54.780 --> 48:59.460
I mean, seems like everything I have faith in

48:59.460 --> 49:01.980
cost me nothin but trouble.

49:08.060 --> 49:12.740
When God chose your kind

49:12.740 --> 49:17.420
as the object of his love....

49:17.420 --> 49:21.660
I was the first in all of heaven
to bow down before you.

49:23.660 --> 49:30.300
My love and my hope for
mankind hasn't lessened yet.

49:33.980 --> 49:37.860
But I have watched you trample that gift.

49:37.860 --> 49:42.180
I've watched you kill each
other over race and greed.

49:42.180 --> 49:46.940
Waging war over dust, rubble
and words in old books.

49:46.940 --> 49:52.060
And yet in the midst of all this darkness

49:52.060 --> 49:54.820
I see some people who will not be bowed.

49:57.180 --> 50:02.180
I see some people
who will not give up.

50:02.700 --> 50:05.740
Even when they know hope is lost.

50:08.040 --> 50:11.920
Some people, who realize that being

50:11.920 --> 50:15.800
lost is so close to being found.

50:17.360 --> 50:19.920
I see you, Jeep.

50:20.720 --> 50:25.160
Fifteen years old, your mother leaves you,
your father withdraws from the world.

50:25.600 --> 50:28.320
And you spend the next five years of your life

50:28.320 --> 50:30.480
helping him find his way home.

50:32.680 --> 50:35.160
You love a woman, who has the child of another,

50:35.160 --> 50:37.760
and you love her making a fool of yourself.

50:39.120 --> 50:41.600
Even though you know she may never
love you the way you love her.

50:44.200 --> 50:47.240
You, Jeep.

50:49.080 --> 50:52.640
You are the reason I still have faith.

50:58.040 --> 51:00.560
It's almost time for the next shift.

51:51.020 --> 51:53.420
You have a question?

51:54.780 --> 51:59.140
I question myself.
So should you.

52:02.780 --> 52:05.860
Since their creation, He's
told us only to love them.

52:08.300 --> 52:10.220
I can not stop.

52:12.220 --> 52:15.940
They brought this judgment upon themselves.
- They are just lost.

52:17.020 --> 52:19.260
It's our place to guide them.

52:19.260 --> 52:21.980
It's my place to obey.

52:22.500 --> 52:25.380
Tell me, Gabriel. 
Do you wish to give Him what 

52:25.380 --> 52:28.300
He wants...or what He needs?

52:28.820 --> 52:32.020
It's not your test, Michael.

52:32.020 --> 52:35.860
How dare you listen to His heart?
- Because He made this one.

52:36.780 --> 52:39.820
It tells me we shouldn't
lose faith now.

52:41.900 --> 52:46.780
It's too late. 
The order has been given.

52:46.780 --> 52:51.220
The weak will turn against the strong,
and we will undo what has been done?

52:51.520 --> 52:54.560
And if you defy Him...

52:54.560 --> 52:57.600
You'll anger Him for the last time.

52:58.240 --> 53:01.040
What if I failed...

53:01.040 --> 53:04.680
Lord's coming to man whether he wishes or not.

53:04.680 --> 53:08.240
The dogs of heaven will be released.

53:37.840 --> 53:39.800
<i>Sandra</i>

53:42.840 --> 53:45.040
<i>Sandra</i>

54:13.900 --> 54:15.820
Howarde?

54:38.980 --> 54:40.980
Howarde.

54:57.820 --> 54:59.740
Help me!

55:04.140 --> 55:08.260
What are you doing?
- He's alive! Let me go!

55:15.540 --> 55:18.140
Mom, what are you doing?
Mom, stop!

55:18.140 --> 55:19.500
Your father is alive!
- He's not, mom!

55:19.500 --> 55:21.420
Let go of me!
God!

55:43.940 --> 55:45.860
No, don't!

55:49.640 --> 55:51.560
Percy?

56:09.860 --> 56:13.700
It's my fault.
I fell asleep.

56:14.580 --> 56:16.780
Dad...
- Don't!

56:20.340 --> 56:24.940
I did this he trusted me.

56:24.940 --> 56:27.900
Just like your mother, I let him down.

56:28.100 --> 56:30.180
Let everybody down.

56:44.900 --> 56:49.620
Here. Mom, If you take
these you'll feel better, Ok?

57:08.400 --> 57:10.520
This is your fault.

57:11.240 --> 57:14.280
We were only here because of you.

57:14.280 --> 57:17.920
We sacrificed everything for you.

57:17.920 --> 57:22.960
No. You wanted to go.
You said you wanted.

57:22.960 --> 57:25.040
I loved my house.

57:26.200 --> 57:29.400
I loved my life, 
and you have ruined it.

57:30.240 --> 57:32.640
You ruined everything!

57:32.880 --> 57:35.320
Everything!
- Enough.

57:35.920 --> 57:39.120
You're just gonna sit here
and torture your daughter like this?

57:39.120 --> 57:42.640
Can you come help me
find a station that actually works?

58:04.960 --> 58:09.320
Wait! Guys, almost got it...
I'm hearin' something!

58:10.460 --> 58:12.820
<i>If you're hearing my voice,
we're getting the first bits</i>

58:12.820 --> 58:16.940
<i>of good news since this
Apocalypse began,</i>

58:16.940 --> 58:19.300
<i>nearly 48 hours ago.</i>

58:19.300 --> 58:22.020
<i>A militia has formed on
the outskirts of Las Vegas</i>

58:22.020 --> 58:24.740
<i>and has begun to
engage those affected.</i>

58:24.740 --> 58:28.220
<i>Getting unconfirmed reports
of other militias gathering</i>

58:28.220 --> 58:32.260
<i>in Death Valley, Zion and
Red Ridge National Park.</i>

58:32.260 --> 58:34.180
Red Ridge, that's only
an hour from here.

58:34.180 --> 58:36.220
Does that mean we can leave?
- No.

58:37.420 --> 58:39.900
We're not going anywhere.
- What?

58:39.900 --> 58:43.020
I don't know about you,
but I gotta get fuck out of here.

58:45.420 --> 58:48.660
I won't risk being on the
move when the baby comes.

58:50.180 --> 58:52.180
It's too dangerous.

58:57.100 --> 59:01.260
Dangerous? 
What the fuck you mean too dangerous?

59:02.360 --> 59:05.960
<i>...strength to survive. And
have mercy for those</i>

59:05.960 --> 59:07.880
<i>who are already lost.</i>

59:41.400 --> 59:43.320
You okay?

59:46.920 --> 59:49.720
The craziest thing is
I don't want this baby.

59:52.680 --> 59:55.120
I even went down to the
clinic, did you know that?

59:56.320 --> 59:58.800
I remember sitting in
the waiting room...

59:58.800 --> 01:00:01.760
absolutely sure I was
doing the right thing.

01:00:04.320 --> 01:00:07.000
Then I started getting this feeling...

01:00:07.000 --> 01:00:13.320
Like if I was, falling into the deepest, 
darkest hole imaginable.

01:00:15.520 --> 01:00:19.480
I couldn't breathe and
either couldn't speak.

01:00:21.920 --> 01:00:28.000
I kept thinking this must be
what death feels like.

01:00:32.480 --> 01:00:35.200
And when they called my name,
I just ran.

01:00:40.060 --> 01:00:42.740
For a long time I...

01:00:43.980 --> 01:00:47.420
I always thought that I could
go back whenever I'd want.

01:00:48.380 --> 01:00:51.620
And end it like,
I'd planned.

01:00:52.780 --> 01:00:57.500
But then I started getting
that damn feeling again

01:00:59.940 --> 01:01:02.420
I knew I had no choice.

01:01:04.100 --> 01:01:07.300
Somehow this had already been decided.

01:01:07.860 --> 01:01:10.460
It made me just...

01:01:12.340 --> 01:01:17.500
Made me hate this
thing growing inside me.

01:01:19.420 --> 01:01:22.020
You shouldn't say
things like that, Charlie.

01:01:23.220 --> 01:01:26.700
It ain't right. 
You'll get through this, 

01:01:26.700 --> 01:01:29.020
I know you will..

01:01:30.740 --> 01:01:32.940
Why do you have so much
faith in me, Jeep?

01:01:35.980 --> 01:01:39.060
God knows I've never given
you or anybody a reason to.

01:01:41.340 --> 01:01:45.740
Or is it just that you don't have any other
hard-luck cases to follow around, is that it?

01:01:48.820 --> 01:01:52.980
No. You're not the only one who’s
had it hard around here, okay?

01:01:53.300 --> 01:01:56.860
Let me know when you stop
feeling sorry for yourself.

01:02:05.540 --> 01:02:10.980
So now you just have to...
- Two clicks. All the way down.

01:02:12.280 --> 01:02:16.480
I dated a marine last summer.
He was kind of a gun freak.

01:02:16.480 --> 01:02:21.040
My parents hated him.
- I bet they did.

01:02:24.080 --> 01:02:29.000
My mom was right. It is
my fault we are here.

01:02:29.000 --> 01:02:32.760
She didn't mean that.
- Yes, she did...

01:02:32.800 --> 01:02:34.680
It's true.

01:02:34.680 --> 01:02:38.040
I mean the only reason why we're
moving is because of me.

01:02:38.040 --> 01:02:41.880
They thought my friends
were a bad influence.

01:02:42.720 --> 01:02:46.280
But I was the bad influence.

01:02:50.960 --> 01:02:53.960
So really fucked up.

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:58.280
When I was a shorty, the
only time my old man ever

01:02:58.280 --> 01:03:01.640
gave me attention was
when I did something bad.

01:03:02.240 --> 01:03:04.800
So you know what I did, right?
- What?

01:03:04.800 --> 01:03:07.560
I got really good at being bad.

01:03:09.200 --> 01:03:14.960
The problem is, when you get older,
when you have a family,

01:03:14.960 --> 01:03:18.400
being bad is not so good.

01:03:31.920 --> 01:03:33.840
Is it over?

01:03:39.960 --> 01:03:44.160
Are we back in business?
- No, I don't think so.

01:03:56.080 --> 01:03:59.600
You better go downstairs
- No, I can handle it.

01:03:59.760 --> 01:04:02.920
Get downstairs.
- No. I can handle it.

01:04:04.640 --> 01:04:06.920
Take this, just in case.

01:04:11.640 --> 01:04:13.560
Get ready.

01:04:22.400 --> 01:04:26.800
Wait a minute.
- Kyle, are they...?

01:04:34.920 --> 01:04:36.840
Kyle!

01:04:43.000 --> 01:04:46.240
It's a trap! 

01:04:46.240 --> 01:04:48.400
They see them coming
and turn their lights on.

01:04:48.400 --> 01:04:52.520
Hey! Get back in your car!
Get back in your car!

01:04:55.000 --> 01:04:56.000
<i>Daddy!<i></i></i>

01:04:57.960 --> 01:04:59.880
They not gonna make it!

01:05:01.160 --> 01:05:03.080
Get in the car!

01:05:24.360 --> 01:05:26.480
Don't, you're gonna hit him!

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:40.640
What the hell is that guy doing? 

01:05:45.800 --> 01:05:49.320
Don't open the door.
If you do, we all die.

01:06:05.040 --> 01:06:06.960
Now what?

01:06:16.540 --> 01:06:18.460
Fooled you.

01:06:21.620 --> 01:06:23.580
Damn it to hell!

01:06:26.500 --> 01:06:29.580
Oh no. Audrey.

01:06:37.020 --> 01:06:38.980
You're gonna die now.

01:06:43.820 --> 01:06:46.740
She's just a kid,
you can't let her die.

01:06:48.220 --> 01:06:50.300
I swear if you don't
do something, I will.

01:07:00.300 --> 01:07:03.300
Wait. You stay here.

01:07:05.820 --> 01:07:07.740
Open the door.

01:07:50.300 --> 01:07:52.220
Come on!
Run!

01:07:54.500 --> 01:07:56.620
I'll get some water.
- Jeep!

01:08:04.780 --> 01:08:08.180
Don't be scared. I just want
to play with your baby.

01:08:31.939 --> 01:08:34.140
Are you hurt?
- Where is he?

01:08:54.979 --> 01:08:56.899
